Kimi.ai open-sources new coding model with 30% fewer reasoning tokens
10,582 Likes
Moonshot AI just dropped
Kimi-K2.7-Code
, a new open-source coding model that is faster, smarter, and cheaper to ru=
n than its predecessor.
The big idea: the model was specifically trained to stop "overthinking." Wh=
en an AI reasons through a problem, it uses tokens, which cost money and ad=
d latency. K2.7 cuts that
reasoning token usage by 30%
, meaning you get better answers while spending less.
Here is what improved over K2.6:
+21.8%
on coding tasks, +11% on general programming, and +31.5% on multi-language =
work across Python, Rust, and Go
Better instruction following on long, complex coding sessions that span man=
y steps
Scores 81.1% on tool-use benchmarks, beating Claude Opus 4.8's 76.4%
You can use it three ways: via the Kimi API at
$0.95 per million input tokens
, through the Kimi Code CLI agent, or self-host the weights for free on Hug=
ging Face. The API is OpenAI and Anthropic SDK compatible, so it is a one-l=
ine swap in your existing code.
